---
title: Harissa Sweet Potato Pita Pockets with Cucumber Dill Salad
description: All hail the pita! It holds pretty much anything you put in its roomy pockets, making it among the most capacious of breads. So if you’re going to make a pita sandwich, it better be fully loaded. This one does not disappoint: in addition to rounds of roasted sweet potato, it’s packed with slices of creamy avocado, an herby cucumber salad, pumpkin seeds, and a spicy harissa mayo.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5c3cb170c445fa2277482006-cabc7683.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/harissa-sweet-potato-pita-pockets-5c3cb170c445fa2277482006-9b78b35c.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 14 g
  sodium: 550 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/harissa-sweet-potato-pita-pockets-5c3cb170c445fa2277482006
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Slice @sweet potatoes{2%units} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @harissa powder{1%tsp} (we'll use more later), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast, flipping halfway through, until tender, about ~{20%minutes}.

Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} (we sent more). Halve @cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise, then slice into thin half-moons. Pick and roughly chop enough fronds from @dill{¼%ounce} to give you 2 tsp. Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1%unit}, then thinly slice.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} (we sent more), a pinch of garlic, and a pinch of harissa powder. Give mixture a taste and add more garlic and harissa powder as desired. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss cucumber, chopped dill, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Cut @whole wheat pitas{2%units} in half to create four pockets and place on another baking sheet. When sweet potatoes are almost done, after 18-20 minutes of roasting, put pitas in oven. Toast until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes} (they should still be soft and flexible).

> If there's room, you can place pitas on the same baking sheet as sweet potatoes instead.

Spread harissa mayo inside each pita half, then fill with sweet potatoes, avocado, a few @pepitas{1%oz}, and a small amount of cucumber salad. Divide stuffed pitas between plates. Add remaining cucumber salad to the side and sprinkle with remaining pepitas.